      5.0 out of 5 stars Detailed Review after Four Days
      Reviewed in India on 18 January 2025
      Colour: Gray + 8GB + 128GB (Wifi) Verified Purchase
      So far the device is perfectly fine. A lot of people saying 'There is no SIM Card slot' are stupid as they've opted for Wi-Fi Variant and those saying it's slow and laggy were the ones who thought 'Let's buy this instead of S9 FE/FE+ to save money'.
      I bought this in on 13/01/2025 under 13k (thanks to SBI) and received next day.
      While recording the unboxing, I checked the body was completely fine and to my shock this variant is manufactured in January 2025 (rather than October 2023). After rebooting, I checked screen specially corners for yellow shift as some reviews said but it was fine. Then camera works fine which is specially designed for documents and if someone is expecting so much then he doesn't know about tablet industry where camera is just for specs.
      The real power of Tab A9 Plus is OneUI, specially if someone already owns a Samsung device. I can't write much about that but OneUI 7.0 is coming February 2025. Speaking of which security updates upto October 2027 is insane along with OneUI 8.0 later. Battery life is great but it takes time to adapt, initially it may seem draining. I charge upyo 80% then replug at 20%. So, basically I am using only 60% (~ 4224 mAh from 7040 mAh). Talking about the usb-c to c cable inside box, I don't use that as I already have a 15W USB-A Adapter, so I bought a USB-A to USB-C (1.5m/black) from another websire ₹399 rather than a thousand rupees 25W adapter since it only supports 15W adaptive charging.
      Coming to the back cover, I would suggest you to buy Robustrion ones rather than it's competitors.

    • sachin
      4.0 out of 5 stars Could be more needed in this price range
      Reviewed in India on 24 October 2024
      Colour: Gray + 8GB + 128GB (Wifi) Verified Purchase
      I recently had the opportunity to use the Samsung Galaxy Tab A9+, and I was really impressed by its performance and features. Here’s a closer look at the pros and cons from my experience.

      Pros:
      Vibrant Display: The 11-inch screen is bright and colorful, providing excellent clarity. It’s great for watching videos, browsing, or reading.

      Generous RAM and Storage: With 8 GB of RAM, multitasking is smooth and efficient. The 128 GB of internal storage offers ample space for apps, media, and files, and you can expand it if you need more.

      User-Friendly Interface: Running on Samsung’s One UI, the interface is intuitive and easy to navigate. It works seamlessly with other Samsung devices, enhancing the overall experience.

      Sturdy Build: The tablet feels solid and well-made, giving it a premium quality. Plus, it’s lightweight, making it easy to carry around.

      Impressive Battery Life: The battery performance is great, allowing for long usage without needing to recharge frequently. It can easily last throughout the day, whether for work or play.

      Good Connectivity Options: With Wi-Fi support, connecting to the internet for streaming, browsing, and downloading is straightforward. It also has a range of apps for productivity and entertainment.

      Cons:
      Camera Quality: While the camera is fine for basic tasks, it doesn’t excel in photography. If high-quality images are important to you, this tablet might not be the best fit.

      Limited Gaming Performance: It handles most everyday tasks well, but you may find it struggles with graphically intensive games. It’s better suited for casual use rather than heavy gaming.

      No Stylus Support: Unlike some other tablets, the Galaxy Tab A9+ doesn’t support a stylus, which could be a drawback for anyone wanting to take handwritten notes or draw.

      No AMOLED Display: The LCD display is good, but it lacks the vibrant colors and deep blacks of AMOLED screens found on some higher-end models.

      Price Point: While it has great features, some might find it a bit pricey compared to other tablets with similar specs, particularly in the budget range.

      Conclusion
      In summary, the Samsung Galaxy Tab A9+ is a well-rounded tablet that shines in display quality, performance, and ease of use. It’s an excellent choice for watching media, light productivity, and everyday tasks. However, if you’re looking for top-notch camera capabilities, heavy gaming performance, or stylus support, you may want to explore other options. For those seeking a reliable and stylish tablet, the Galaxy Tab A9+ is definitely worth considering.
